        "content": "type: search_result\ntitle: 10 train trips to take in 2026 – US Train Travel Guide\nurl: \"https://amtrakguide.com/2025/12/14/train-trips-2026/\"\ndescription: \"The Coast Starlight is a must-do route on the West Coast and an excellent choice for first-time long-distance train travelers. This scenic two-day, one-night journey links Southern California’s beaches with the mountains and forests of the Pacific Northwest, with the option to use airports in Los Angeles, Burbank, Santa Barbara, Portland, and Seattle. Summer is the most popular time to ride, so book early or plan your trip before Memorial Day weekend or just after Labor Day weekend for fewer crowds.\"\npage_age: \"March 25, 2026\"\nprofile_name: Amtrak Guide\nmeta_url_favicon: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/lUS_FiAylsSNfDu_nXs6XjVzeb9_6QMFCtgqrIapM9c/rs:fit:32:32:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cDovL2Zhdmlj/b25zLnNlYXJjaC5i/cmF2ZS5jb20vaWNv/bnMvNTMzZTY1NmQy/YTYxMDg3MjI3NTk2/ZjI5Nzk1YzVmZjI2/OGU4NWRmZjdkOTNj/MzIzNjhiYjQ1Y2Iz/YTRjY2QxNS9hbXRy/YWtndWlkZS5jb20v\"\nthumbnail_src: \"https://imgs.search.brave.com/3iKF5XgBcj7Fpab4cthTTJO1JpYJUPc_dbyi1AsKls4/rs:fit:200:200:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53/cC5jb20vYW10cmFr/Z3VpZGUuY29tL3dw/LWNvbnRlbnQvdXBs/b2Fkcy8yMDI1LzEy/L2NvYXN0X3N0YXJs/aWdodF9jYXNjYWRl/cy5qcGc_Zml0PTEy/MDAlMkM5MDgmIzAz/ODtzc2w9MQ\"\nthumbnail_original: \"https://i0.wp.com/amtrakguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/coast_starlight_cascades.jpg?fit=1200%2C908&#038;ssl=1\"\nextra_snippets: \"Train travel in the United States is becoming increasingly popular, with Amtrak ridership up 5.1% in fiscal year 2025. Traveling by train offers a relaxing alternative to flying or driving, with un…|Choose from many Amtrak, SEPTA and NJ Transit trains to reach the historic 30th Street Station, which is conveniently located near all the action. Tip: Use Google Maps to view all your train options. ... In 2026, the weekend before Fat Tuesday overlaps with Presidents Day weekend, meaning Mardi Gras in New Orleans will likely be even more crowded than usual.|The Coast Starlight is a must-do route on the West Coast and an excellent choice for first-time long-distance train travelers. This scenic two-day, one-night journey links Southern California’s beaches with the mountains and forests of the Pacific Northwest, with the option to use airports in Los Angeles, Burbank, Santa Barbara, Portland, and Seattle. Summer is the most popular time to ride, so book early or plan your trip before Memorial Day weekend or just after Labor Day weekend for fewer crowds.|To avoid expensive flights, heavy car traffic, and rideshare surge pricing, consider arriving by train instead. Four Amtrak routes travel to the New Orleans Union Passenger Terminal, which is within walking distance of numerous hotels and the French Quarter. ... Tucked away in the Colorado Rocky Mountains, the Winter Park Resort is famous for its world-class ski slopes and alpine slide. It’s an easy getaway from Denver, with a travel time of only 2.5 hours on the seasonal Winter Park Express train and the long-distance California Zephyr.\"\nhash: 534aba6c7beded27\nembed_ref: amtrakguide.com-OiY\napp_id: web\nskill_id: search",
